 ANOTHER batch of 331 stranded Nigerians in United Arab Emirate have arrived the country, The Nation learnt. The evacuees arrived the Nnamdi Azikiwe Intâ€™l Airport, Abuja, on Friday afternoon, 7th August, 2020. This brings the number of evacuees from the UAE to a total of 2,042. The country has successfully evacuated about 8,000 Nigerians stranded in various countries abroad since the global lockdown in March 2020 due to the Covid-19 pandemic. According to a tweet by Nigerians in Diaspora Commission (NIDCOM), all evacuees tested negative to Covid-19. The returnees are expected to proceed on a 14 day self-isolation in accordance to the Presidential Taskforce (PTF) on Covid-19 and Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC).